</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1965,2026]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,716]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Male. Integument reddish brown. Ventral region of the body with yellowish pubescence. Head with yellowish and whitish pubescence. Frons lacks erect seta near inner margin of lower ocular lobe. Lower eye lobe about twice as wide as the upper lobe. Apical segment of labial palp as long as preceding and basal about 
<number box="[1196,1206,151,175]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1217,1231,151,175]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as apical. Apical segment of maxillary palps twice as long as preceding. Antennae (Figs 10, 97) with sexual dimorphism, long, exceeding elytral apex at antennomere 
<quantity box="[654,698,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
males and 
<quantity box="[825,868,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
females. Scape with yellowish pubescence in dorsal region and whitish in ventral, pedicel with whitish pubescence on basal half and yellowish pubescence on apical half. Antennae with whitish pubescence, except: on apical third or half with brown pubescence and antennomeres 
<number box="[1422,1436,296,319]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="7.0">7</number>
and 
<number box="[198,212,332,356]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="9.0">9</number>
entirely brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Prothorax almost twice as wide as long; covered with yellowish pubescence and pronotum with some spots of whitish pubescence. Pronotum anterior margin distinctly sinuous, with interrupted row of coarse punctures; two pairs of coarse punctures near posterior margin. Metasternum with longitudinal median sulcus reaching anterior margin. Scutellum with yellowish pubescence.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Elytra about 4.0 to 
<number box="[427,462,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.5">4.5</number>
times as long as prothorax; apices obliquely truncate; pubescence mostly yellowish brown, except: basal 
<number box="[389,399,548,572]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[409,425,548,572]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.0">4</number>
with narrow and irregular band of dark brown pubescence; large median irregular band of yellowish pubescence bordered by whitish and dark brown pubescence; irregular spots of whitish pubescence on apical third. Narrow longitudinal ridge follows the elytral suture from the median region to the apex. Legs with yellowish pubescence; tibiae apical half with dark brown pubescence and short black erect setae. Urosternite 
<number box="[1422,1436,655,679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="5.0">5</number>
rounded at apex in females, and truncate in males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
